Package: InnoPlexR
Type: Package
Title: Modelling Innovation Systems Through Multiplex Networks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Marcus", "Zabel", email = "m.t.zabel@students.nl", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for constructing and analyzing multiplex networks in the
    context of innovation systems research. Supports the integration of patent,
    publication, and CORDIS funding data as separate network layers. Provides
    functions for building multiplex objects from igraph layers, computing
    supra-adjacency and supra-Laplacian matrices, and calculating multiplex
    centrality measures including eigenvector centrality, PageRank, geodesic
    betweenness, random-walk betweenness, and local clustering coefficients.
    Also supports conversion to Infomap format and extraction of connected
    components.
